    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nI want to create a preview for command \":Cfilter\", unfortunately, quickfix buffer doesn't seem to allow preview to modify it\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Content of `repro.lua`\n```lua\nlocal function cmd_preview(opts, preview_ns, preview_buf)\n  local qfbufnr = vim.fn.getqflist({ qfbufnr = 0 }).qfbufnr ---@type number\n  vim.api.nvim_buf_set_lines(qfbufnr, 0, -1, false, { opts.args })\n  -- vim.hl.range(qfbufnr, preview_ns, 'IncSearch', { 0, 0 }, { #opts.args, #opts.args })\n  return 1\nend\n\nvim.api.nvim_create_user_command('Test', function() end, {\n\tpreview = cmd_preview,\n\tnargs = '+'\n})\n```\n2. git clone --depth=1 https://github.com/neovim/neovim\n3. cd neovim\n4. nvim --clean -u repro.lua\n5. `:grep cfilter`\n6. `:copen`\n7. Type `:Test args`\n8. The content of the quickfix buffer doesn't change at all. Now exit Nvim\n9. Now comment the line `vim.api.nvim_buf_set_lines ...` in file repro.lua and uncomment the line `vim.hl.range`\n10. Do from step 4 to step 7 again. You can now see the highlight region change as you type the argument.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nQuickfix buffer should change the content temporarily as I type command `:Test` in step 7\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.12.0-dev-63a7b92e58\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nN/A\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nKubuntu 24.04.1\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nKonsole 23.08.5\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nfrom source",
